      "content": "no i dont think its just stress. stress doesn't make my teeth ache in a specific pitch. it felt like his voice hit a micro-tone that was just... off. like a dissonant chord in music. it wasn't just an intuition, it was a physical sensation of a lie. is there any way that a change in vocal frequency could actually be tied to what's going on in someone's head? like, could the physical mechanics of lying actually change the resonance of a person's voice?",
